  "prompt": "I know I can do best but still I can't do Nothing?",
  "response": "It sounds like you're feeling stuck or overwhelmed, even though you believe in your potential. This is a common experience, and it\u2019s important to be kind to yourself during these moments. Here are a few steps to help you break through:\n\n1. **Reframe Your Thoughts**: Instead of thinking, \"I can't do anything,\" try saying, \"I\u2019m feeling stuck right now, but I have the ability to take small steps.\" Acknowledging your feelings without judgment can help you move forward.\n\n2. **Start Small**: Break down your goals into tiny, manageable tasks. Even something as simple as writing down your thoughts or making a to-do list can help you regain a sense of control.\n\n3. **Focus on Progress, Not Perfection**: Remember, small steps are still progress. Celebrate even the smallest wins\u2014they add up over time.\n\n4. **Ask for Support**: Sometimes, sharing your struggles with someone you trust can give you a fresh perspective or the encouragement you need.\n\n5. **Be Patient with Yourself**: Growth takes time. It\u2019s okay to feel stuck; it doesn\u2019t mean you\u2019re incapable. You\u2019re just in a phase of figuring things out.\n\nYou\u2019re not alone in this, and you *can* move forward. Even if it feels like nothing is happening right now, every effort you make is a step in the right direction. Keep going\u2014you\u2019ve got this! \ud83c\udf1f",
